<br>
I would hope that the focus would shift towards what people have standing concerns for...you know- players who have been here for years and play for months just to see that some door has been fixed in ancient zone that saw its last heavy usage back in the velious era. LoY is another example of mostly wasted effort, an expansion that brought little or nothing to the game. I dont know for sure that much attention was payed to all of this, but it surely seems so. If anything, I would prefer to have more focus towards higher end issues, anything below 30 doesnt need to be looked into. Hello: would the game really be that much more dynamic and interesting with better quests for levels that take a day to get out of?<br>
<br>
my point is that I'd like to see more rescource/focus going to the area where players have more strong concern. level 8 quests, who really cares or notices it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganwolfxev>LoganwolfXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/03 12:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Back Burner&quot;</span><hr size=1> Actually, I am quite happy with EQ myself.<br>
