<br>
I was with a 56 bst in Chardok, i though hmm, dungeon, must be good xp. So i killed there solo, till the gatehouse then went back to zi. <br>
But after some hours, i noticed, xp barely rises. So i loaded up my OT gate hammer and procced to my lovely outpost book.<br>
And then i just went to POJ zone-m for solo xp, which was way and way better. YET, it was also easier!!<br>
<br>
This is one of the reasons people don't go to old zones that much anymore, the xp reward for the amount of efford is way out of balance compared to the xp reward for the amount of efford in a pop zone. Pop zones are easier i think. Sure mobs hit harder, but it takes less efford to get better xp.<br>
<br>
Other problems with older zones:<br>
<br>
First, people want fast a group, so they go to zones, that are very close by. They do not walk to chardok/kedge/sebilis/solB and such to see if there is an opening there.<br>
Solution, put again more books in different zones.<br>
<br>
Second, a lot of people don't have loads of cleric/necro friends around. So if they die in a dungeon, with no graveyard, they got a SERIOUS problem. I really suggest to put graveyards in all zones. It's plain stupid, that only the highest level people have graveyards in their xp zones.<br>
<br>
Third, the xp is barely worth it anymore.<br>
I noticed lvl 54 to 60 is way and way tougher to get then 60 to 65 plus several aa.<br>
<br>
Fourth, about loy zones, these zones have way and way too many mobs around. There is barely a place where you can set up a camp. And NO, people don't want to set up camp on spots, where a mob can respawn in the middle of their camp.<br>
We just want to have fun and no stress about camp-spawn-adds.<br>
<br>
