 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qhue>Qhue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/03 7:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> the BackBurner</span><hr size=1> Why do we think its on the back burner?  Because there is zero evidence that its not on the back burner!<br>
<br>
Planes of Power, upon release, had a rich and engaging storyline that hinted at conspiracy, corruption and collusion among the very gods themselves!  We had interactions with NPCs that had both personal stories of strife with the gods but with an overarching theme that interconnected each of these individual tragedies into a more concrete whole : a conspiracy against Zebuxoruk the very enlightened mortal who first brought godlike power ot mortals like us the player-characters.<br>
<br>
Everyone was pumped about both the intriguing content (GRummus was a deceptively HARD mob to kill!) concepts as well as the evolving storyline as they progressed quickly through the inital stages of PoP....  far TOO quickly as it turns out because rich evidence of the intermingled plot vanishes once the playerbase ran smack into the Rathe roadblock.  Even without the Rathe issue there is precious little evidence of the plotline anymore as guilds have spent months and months on the same &quot;page&quot; of the storyline...so long in fact that nearly everyone has forgotten why they were there in the first place!   Time itself (from what I have been able to glean) which should have a BIG recap of the plotline to date when you first enter the zone and do the initial encounters starts out with a 4 elemental + undead minion encounter that seems to come out of left field and involve ZERO major characters!<br>
<br>
Now with flagging being removed for everything pre-Elemental as well as cutting out any required flagging for Time access it seems the Dev Team is just throwing up their hands and saying &quot;fine you win...go nuts!&quot; and tossing the tattered remnants of the plotline on the ground.<br>
<br>
Legacy of Ykesha had a central plotline in all the Flash-episodic prequels that teased us prior to its release...but ZERO plotline when you actually get into the expansion area!<br>
<br>
SoE has a massive trackrecord now of building up a new plotline trhough use of Hammerfel's wonderful puzzles and websites and not following through on any of them by releasing unfinished products that then only ever get made workable in the sense that there is a dungeon and loot drops there to make people satiated.<br>
<br>
<br>
Everquest expnasions to date are a series of novels that no one has ever finished.  <br>
<br>
Ruins of Kunark -- a novel about a elven princess kidnapped to a land ruled by evil lizardmen and where Dragons exist as the power behind many thrones.... only we never see the princess much less rescue her and the Ring of Scale are just a bunch of mobs that drop nice items.<br>
<br>
Scars of Velious -- a novel about exploration into the frozen wasteland of velious where Veeshan's claws first struck Norrath and where her brood reside.  Along the way the characters encounter the war between the Ice Dwarves and the Giants as well as the conflicts between the Giants and the ancient Dragons who make their home in Veeshans Temple.   Tunare has her own inroads into this frozen continent for reasons that no one seems to understand and the Prince of Mirth Bristlebane has a completely unfinished zone dedicated seemingly to a puppetshow with no plot.  The conflict with the Dragons just leads to another slaughter of Dragons for loot without even a lick of flavor text.  The Ice Dwarves and giants have a series of epic encounters but it fizzles out with the plotline ending with the final shawl quest.  The Avatar of War is a penultimate encounter with no follow through!   Everyone stands in Vulak's chamber after he dies and goes &quot;errr what was the point?&quot;.... Oh and the world gets annihilated after the Sleeper is Awakened, but actually waking him up doesnt seem to change anything and several years after doing so everything is pretty peachy keen so it seems rather silly that anyone bothered to lock him up in the first place!<br>
<br>
Shadows of Luclin -- All about what happened to the ancient empires of Norrath, the Combine Empire and the Shissar are both exiled to the surface of one of Norrath's Moons.  Trapped there by the machinations of...well its presumed Luclin herself only we never SEE Luclin, or Tsaph Katta, or get any good reason why Luclin suddenly becomes reachable etc.   Its nearly 2 years later that someone bothers to touch on the Takashi - Khati Sha connection and weave that back into the plotline that links the Grimlings to the Shissar...maybe in another 2 years Luclin will appear and explain why she was Torturing Grieg, who Katta really was, and why she has interfered in the destiny of mortals down on Norrath by trapping people on her moon.<br>
<br>
Plane of Power I touched on above and no one has seen Zebuxoruk much less rescued him, but all the fine detail to plot and the complex story that was setup with countless man hours of flavor text and chatty NPCs upon release has degraded into tuning mobs that drop elemental molds.<br>
<br>
<br>
E3 came and went and there was NO new official announcement of an Everquest expansion or even ackowledgement that the game, as it exists, is no longer fun.<br>
<br>
Everytime a solution is added to the game that essentially just involves keeping the players happpy with token ube loot that pushes people further and further towards other games.  <br>
<br>
There are people who could and WOULD fix many of the problems that are endemic to Everquest from a play-value aspect, the fact that it hasnt been done is proof that its on the Backburner as far as SoE is concerned and by willfully letting it continue it has critically damaged SoEs reputation as being able to provide quality entertainment.<br>
